# Data and persistence

## Repository layer
- For any module that performs non-trivial or reusable DB access, introduce a dedicated repository (e.g. `repository/<module>.repository.ts`) and keep services free of raw TypeORM calls.
- Simple CRUD that is only used in one service may stay in the service.

## Migrations
- Migrations must be named with a timestamp prefix and a short slug (e.g. `1734123456789-add-user-kyc-fields.ts`).
- Never edit an already-applied migration; add a new one for fixes.

## Idempotency
- Order, payment, and ledger writes must be idempotent (idempotency key or unique constraint).
- Document idempotency in MODULE_DOC and in API contracts.
